RELY-SE — Artifact Requirements
================================

Architecture
------------
x86_64 (tested). No GPU or specialized hardware required.
Should also run on ARM64 (e.g., Apple Silicon) but this has not
been explicitly verified by the authors.

Operating System
----------------
- Ubuntu 22.04 LTS (primary test environment)
- macOS 13+ (tested)
- Windows via WSL2 should work but is untested.

Software Dependencies
----------------------
- Python 3.11 or later
- pip
- All Python dependencies are pinned in requirements.txt at the
  repository root and installed via:
      pip install -r requirements.txt
  Key dependencies: streamlit>=1.32.0, pandas>=2.0.0, numpy>=1.24.0,
  plotly>=5.18.0, datasets>=2.14.0 (used by select_tasks.py to
  fetch SWE-bench Lite task data).
- No compiled/native dependencies; pure Python application.
- No Docker or VM image is provided; the artifact runs directly
  via Python and pip on any system meeting the above.

Hardware
--------
- Minimum 8 GB RAM
- Minimum ~500 MB free disk space (sample traces + dependencies)
- No GPU required

Network
-------
- Required only for:
  (a) select_tasks.py, to download SWE-bench Lite task metadata via
      the datasets package, and
  (b) run_aider.py, to call the Anthropic API (or another LLM
      provider configured for Aider).
- Not required for the smoke test (generate_sample_traces.py +
  dashboard.py), which runs entirely offline on synthetic data.

External Services / API Keys
------------------------------
- An Anthropic API key (or equivalent LLM provider key supported
  by Aider) is required only to reproduce live agent execution
  (Option B in Quick Start / the paper's Aider results).
  Not required to run the smoke test or explore the dashboard
  with bundled sample data.
- No rate-limited or reviewer-specific credentials are required;
  reviewers may use their own API key or skip live execution and
  rely on the 135 traces already bundled in the repository/archive.

Estimated Time
--------------
- Installation: < 10 minutes
- Smoke test: < 5 minutes
- Full paper reproduction (live Aider run, 15 tasks x 3 trials):
  1-2 hours, dependent on API latency
